#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:7
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:9
msgid ""
"AzireVPN is an international VPN provider, co-locating in multiple "
"datacenters and offering secure tunneling in respect to privacy. To set "
"up a WireGuard VPN to AzireVPN we assume you are familiar with the "
"concepts of WireGuard you that you have read the basic howto :doc"
":`wireguard-client`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:15
msgid "Step 1 - Get AzireVPN configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:17
msgid ""
"For an automated rollout of configuration, AzireVPN will create a private"
" key in your browser and send the public key via an API call to their "
"servers. To get a configuration login to your account_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:23
msgid ""
"Via **Options** you can select the country where you want to break out, "
"choose a port (default ist fine), and set the protocol to tunnel (we only"
" cover IPv4)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:26
msgid ""
"Hit **Download** at the end of the page to get the preconfigured text "
"file and open it in your favorite text editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:31
msgid "Step 2 - Setup WireGuard Instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:33
msgid ""
"Go to tab **Local** and create a new instance. Give it a **Name** and set"
" a desired **Listen Port**. If you have more than one server instance be "
"aware that you can use the **Listen Port** only once. In the field "
"**Private Key** insert the value from your text file and leave **Public "
"Key** empty. **DNS** and **Tunnel Address** has also to be taken from the"
" configuration. Hit **Save** and go to **Endpoint** tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:39
msgid ""
"On **Endpoint** tab create a new Endpoint, give it a **Name**, set "
"0.0.0.0/0 in **Allowed IPs** and set the DNS name from your configuration"
" in **Endpoint Address**. Don't forget to do this also for the port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:42
msgid ""
"Go back to tab **Local**, open the instance and choose the newly created "
"endpoint in **Peers**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:44
msgid ""
"Now we can **Enable** the VPN in tab **General** and continue with the "
"setup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:48
msgid "Step 3 - Assignments and Routing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:50
msgid ""
"To let you internal clients go through the tunnel you have to add a NAT "
"entry. Go to :menuselection:`Firewall --> NAT --> Outbound` and add a "
"rule. Check that rule generation is set to manual or hybrid. Add a rule "
"and select Wireguard as **Interface**. **Source** should be your LAN "
"network and set **Translation / target** to **interface address**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/wireguard-client-azire.rst:55
msgid ""
"When assigning interfaces we can also add gateways to them. This would  "
"offer you the chance to balance traffic via different VPN providers or do"
" more complex routing scenarios."
msgstr ""

